1001
00:53:32.074 --> 00:53:37.380
And I need to get
this mall locked down
from the inside immediately.

1002
00:53:37.446 --> 00:53:40.350
Why don't we just
start wasting hostages?
That'll stop them.

1003
00:53:40.417 --> 00:53:42.419
Well. that's one way
to go. but our hostages

1004
00:53:42.485 --> 00:53:44.821
are the only thing
keeping the cops outside.

1005
00:53:52.962 --> 00:53:54.497
(SIREN WAILS)

1006
00:53:59.402 --> 00:54:01.237
I'm Commander Kent.
My team is deploying.

1007
00:54:01.303 --> 00:54:03.005
I need this
location secured.

1008
00:54:03.072 --> 00:54:03.072
We got a three-block
perimeter...

1009
00:54:03.072 --> 00:54:04.173
Establish a perimeter

1010
00:54:04.240 --> 00:54:05.208
and get all these
people out of here.

1011
00:54:05.274 --> 00:54:06.542
Whoa. whoa. this is
all done already.

1012
00:54:06.609 --> 00:54:08.611
My men are gonna do it
again. the right way.

1013
00:54:08.677 --> 00:54:11.080
Have your guys fall
back. now. Have there
been any demands?

1014
00:54:11.147 --> 00:54:13.282
A Happy Meal and
absolute silence.

1015
00:54:13.349 --> 00:54:14.751
Well. let's make
some noise.

1016
00:54:14.817 --> 00:54:18.153
I got snipers at the ready.
communications in check.

1017
00:54:18.220 --> 00:54:20.190
Let's tap into security now.
and let's get some visuals.

1018
00:54:20.256 --> 00:54:21.690
You can't.
They knocked out
the video cameras.

1019
00:54:21.757 --> 00:54:24.360
I'll be ready to take
on-scene command in

1020
00:54:24.426 --> 00:54:27.764
three. two. one.
I'm in charge.

1021
00:54:57.961 --> 00:55:00.463
Brooks. I'm observing
the bank now.

1022
00:55:01.697 --> 00:55:04.634
They got one assailant
guarding the hostages.

1023
00:55:06.802 --> 00:55:08.605
There she is.

1024
00:55:08.671 --> 00:55:11.941
My. God.
You are my angel pie.

1025
00:55:14.844 --> 00:55:17.880
<i> Here come
 the love sweats.</i>

1026
00:55:17.947 --> 00:55:20.083
Paul. your radio's
still on.

1027
00:55:22.552 --> 00:55:23.953
Roger that.

1028
00:55:24.020 --> 00:55:25.487
What's going on?
Who is that?

1029
00:55:25.554 --> 00:55:27.957
We got a guy
on the inside.

1030
00:55:28.023 --> 00:55:30.393
Don't tell me one
of your beat cops is
trying to be a hero.

1031
00:55:30.460 --> 00:55:32.729
No. he's neither.
His name is Blart.

1032
00:55:32.795 --> 00:55:34.964
He's one of my
security guards.

1033
00:55:35.031 --> 00:55:35.031
Wait a minute. Blart?

1034
00:55:35.031 --> 00:55:37.333
Yeah.

1035
00:55:37.400 --> 00:55:37.400
Paul Blart?

1036
00:55:37.400 --> 00:55:39.001
Yeah.

1037
00:55:39.068 --> 00:55:43.172
Are you kidding me? We used
to abuse that loser in
high school. Give me that.

1038
00:55:43.239 --> 00:55:46.042
Blart. This is
Commander James Kent.

1039
00:55:46.109 --> 00:55:47.777
New Jersey SWAT.

1040
00:55:47.843 --> 00:55:50.980
We went to high
school together.
Remember?

1041
00:55:51.047 --> 00:55:54.450
I set you on fire at
the pancake festival?

1042
00:55:54.516 --> 00:55:56.953
Oh. yeah. Hey. Jimmy.

1043
00:55:57.020 --> 00:55:59.122
<i> Go Green Hawks.</i>

1044
00:55:59.189 --> 00:56:03.092
Yeah. listen. I've got
50 highly trained. armed
professionals out here.

1045
00:56:03.159 --> 00:56:05.261
At my command.
we are retaking
this location.

1046
00:56:05.328 --> 00:56:08.431
and there's no way I'm
compromising this mission
so that some mall monitor

1047
00:56:08.498 --> 00:56:11.701
who used to eat lunch
with his imaginary
friend can screw it up.

1048
00:56:11.767 --> 00:56:13.235
Sorry. Jimmy.
I had the button pressed.

1049
00:56:13.302 --> 00:56:16.305
All I heard was
"lunch" and "friend."

1050
00:56:16.372 --> 00:56:18.607
Could you do me a favor
and put Chief Brooks back on?

1051
00:56:18.674 --> 00:56:19.843
<i> Listen to me. Blart.</i>

1052
00:56:19.909 --> 00:56:22.112
you are no longer
communicating with
Chief Brooks.

1053
00:56:22.178 --> 00:56:23.913
Is that clear?

1054
00:56:24.847 --> 00:56:25.948
<i> (STATIC BUZZES)</i>

1055
00:56:26.015 --> 00:56:27.550
Hello?

1056
00:56:27.617 --> 00:56:29.084
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1057
00:56:29.151 --> 00:56:30.386
Hello?

1058
00:56:30.453 --> 00:56:34.724
Yeah? Oh. hey. Paul.
how you doing?

1059
00:56:34.790 --> 00:56:37.826
Well. it looks like
they moved the hostages
into the teller area.

1060
00:56:37.893 --> 00:56:40.029
I'm gonna get
a closer look.

1061
00:57:20.803 --> 00:57:21.905
Veck.

1062
00:57:24.607 --> 00:57:25.909
PRANCER: There he is!

1063
00:57:27.943 --> 00:57:29.445
Everyone in
the back room. now!

1064
00:57:29.512 --> 00:57:32.615
COMET: Come on. move. move!
Let's get in the back. huh?

1065
00:57:32.681 --> 00:57:35.818
(PANTING) Brooks.
I lost visual
on the hostages.

1066
00:57:35.884 --> 00:57:37.320
I couldn't get them out.

1067
00:57:37.387 --> 00:57:40.523
But I know who the
leader is. It's Veck.

1068
00:57:40.590 --> 00:57:42.858
Veck? The trainee?

1069
00:57:42.925 --> 00:57:45.161
No. The brainee.

1070
00:57:45.227 --> 00:57:47.062
I don't believe this.

1071
00:57:47.129 --> 00:57:48.398
I'll pass it on to Howard.

1072
00:57:58.741 --> 00:58:00.043
(PANTING)

1073
00:58:01.477 --> 00:58:03.146
(GRUNTING)

1074
00:58:04.480 --> 00:58:05.681
Oh. God.

1075
00:58:05.747 --> 00:58:07.717
Trapped is fine by me.

1076
00:58:07.784 --> 00:58:10.520
<i> AUTOMATED VOICE:
 Commence tanning.
 Three. two. one.</i>

1077
00:58:17.793 --> 00:58:19.462
(SPITTING)

1078
00:58:21.197 --> 00:58:22.499
(YELLING)

1079
00:58:23.265 --> 00:58:24.567
(SCREAMS)

1080
00:58:35.178 --> 00:58:36.445
(EXCLAIMS)

1081
00:58:36.512 --> 00:58:37.614
Yeah!

1082
00:58:47.456 --> 00:58:48.525
Yes!

1083
00:59:02.071 --> 00:59:03.372
(GUN FIRING)

1084
00:59:03.439 --> 00:59:05.742
Time for some
big-game hunting.

1085
00:59:16.753 --> 00:59:17.820
(TOY SQUEAKING)

1086
00:59:17.886 --> 00:59:19.355
(GRUNTING)

1087
00:59:26.295 --> 00:59:27.363
(GROANING)

1088
00:59:30.433 --> 00:59:33.002
Open. open. open!
Thank God.

1089
00:59:37.573 --> 00:59:39.375
(PANTING) Oh. no.

1090
00:59:39.442 --> 00:59:41.477
(YELLING)

1091
00:59:41.543 --> 00:59:46.683
Sir! Sir! Sir!
Sir! Sir! Sir!
We get it!

1092
00:59:48.150 --> 00:59:49.419
(GRUNTS)

1093
00:59:52.588 --> 00:59:54.624
Get him! Get him! Get him!

1094
01:00:01.364 --> 01:00:02.899
You better run.

1095
01:00:06.202 --> 01:00:07.469
Rudolph. where are you?

1096
01:00:07.536 --> 01:00:09.205
<i> RUDOLPH: I'm about
 to end this.</i>

1097
01:00:10.706 --> 01:00:12.475
(GRUNTS)

1098
01:00:13.176 --> 01:00:14.577
(GRUNTING)

1099
01:00:18.580 --> 01:00:20.183
(PAUL GROANING)

1100
01:00:22.518 --> 01:00:25.121
Amy. huh?
What a coincidence.

1101
01:00:25.187 --> 01:00:27.923
We got a cute little
redhead down at the bank
named Amy.

1102
01:00:27.990 --> 01:00:29.258
Strawberry blonde.
actually.

1103
01:00:29.325 --> 01:00:30.426
Yeah?

1104
01:00:30.493 --> 01:00:33.129
Well. I guess I know
who I'm killing first.

1105
01:00:33.195 --> 01:00:35.264
Catch you later!

1106
01:00:35.331 --> 01:00:38.134
Yeah? Well. it looks like
you just ran out of mall.

1107
01:00:38.201 --> 01:00:41.170
It'll be over quick.
She won't feel a thing.

1108
01:00:43.105 --> 01:00:44.407
(GRUNTS)

1109
01:00:58.788 --> 01:01:00.089
(YELLING)

1110
01:01:01.090 --> 01:01:02.725
(BOTH SCREAMING)

1111
01:01:07.497 --> 01:01:08.831
(GRUNTS)

1112
01:01:25.214 --> 01:01:26.449
(PANTS)

1113
01:01:28.517 --> 01:01:31.487
You aren't gonna touch her.
but you are gonna feel this.

1114
01:01:31.554 --> 01:01:32.822
(GRUNTS)

1115
01:01:35.591 --> 01:01:36.925
(GROANS)

1116
01:01:36.992 --> 01:01:39.162
Nobody wins
with a head butt.

1117
01:01:44.299 --> 01:01:45.601
(BEEPING)

1118
01:01:58.947 --> 01:01:58.947
Give me your cell phone.

1119
01:01:58.947 --> 01:02:00.983
I don't have one.

1120
01:02:01.050 --> 01:02:03.185
What are you talking about?
Every kid has a cell phone.

1121
01:02:03.252 --> 01:02:05.588
I prefer handwritten
sentiments.

1122
01:02:07.122 --> 01:02:09.792
Who are these
sloppy joes for?

1123
01:02:09.858 --> 01:02:11.561
And who gave you this?

1124
01:02:11.627 --> 01:02:13.062
They're mine.

1125
01:02:13.128 --> 01:02:14.897
I'm late for my shift
at Foot Locker.

1126
01:02:15.765 --> 01:02:19.401
<i> (RADIO CHATTERING)</i>

1127
01:02:19.468 --> 01:02:23.172
We're getting
the leader on the horn.
He wants to talk to you.

1128
01:02:23.238 --> 01:02:25.874
Silence. my ass.

1129
01:02:25.941 --> 01:02:27.876
What's the matter?
Throw a few jabs your way.

1130
01:02:27.943 --> 01:02:31.614
you curl up in a corner.
suck your thumb?

1131
01:02:31.680 --> 01:02:33.415
If you don't go
toe-to-toe
with that scumbag.

1132
01:02:33.482 --> 01:02:35.718
he's gonna roll over
on you all night long.

1133
01:02:35.785 --> 01:02:37.887
It's all right.
That's not my style.

1134
01:02:37.953 --> 01:02:44.126
Well. just in case.
I wrote down a couple of
clever comebacks. like...

1135
01:02:44.193 --> 01:02:45.895
Here.

1136
01:02:45.961 --> 01:02:45.961
This is what
you been doing?

1137
01:02:45.961 --> 01:02:48.296
Mmm-hmm.

1138
01:02:48.363 --> 01:02:50.566
"Yeah. you and what army?"

1139
01:02:52.334 --> 01:02:53.636
What's wrong with that?

1140
01:02:53.702 --> 01:02:55.071
He has an army.

1141
01:03:02.044 --> 01:03:04.981
Everyone deserves a card
on their birthday.

1142
01:03:19.395 --> 01:03:20.730
(YELLING)

1143
01:03:29.104 --> 01:03:31.740
So when you and Rudolph
were laughing it up
back at the crib

1144
01:03:31.807 --> 01:03:34.276
about how easy all
this was gonna be.
were you guys like.

1145
01:03:34.343 --> 01:03:37.679
"Man. any brain-dead
mall cop that gets in the
way is gonna get smoked"?

1146
01:03:37.746 --> 01:03:40.449
And then... And then what?
You guys all high-fived?

1147
01:03:40.516 --> 01:03:41.650
Veck. this guard is...

1148
01:03:41.717 --> 01:03:45.053
Winning! I know this.
because I am all set!

1149
01:03:45.120 --> 01:03:48.424
But sadly. no codes!

1150
01:03:48.490 --> 01:03:52.862
And I'd say. considering
all the luxury items
that I have stacked up

1151
01:03:52.929 --> 01:03:55.164
in my Amazon shopping cart.

1152
01:03:55.231 --> 01:03:58.600
situation unacceptable!

1153
01:03:58.667 --> 01:04:00.703
No. no. no. no. no. no.
He looking.

1154
01:04:01.403 --> 01:04:02.905
Give me a gun.

1155
01:04:02.971 --> 01:04:04.240
(GUN CLICKS)

1156
01:04:05.140 --> 01:04:07.810
Put it down.
Put it down.

1157
01:04:07.877 --> 01:04:09.412
What are you
nodding about?

1158
01:04:09.478 --> 01:04:13.282
I was just wondering.
were you serious
about that Happy Meal?

1159
01:04:15.851 --> 01:04:17.453
It isn't coming. is it?

1160
01:04:17.520 --> 01:04:19.055
(PHONE RINGING)

1161
01:04:21.323 --> 01:04:23.024
What?

1162
01:04:23.091 --> 01:04:24.659
This is Commander
James Kent.
New Jersey SWAT.

1163
01:04:24.726 --> 01:04:26.061
You wanted to speak to me?

1164
01:04:26.128 --> 01:04:29.131
I just wanna make sure that
no one does anything stupid.

1165
01:04:29.197 --> 01:04:32.268
You should know my men are
deployed and ready to bring
this thing to a resolution.

1166
01:04:32.335 --> 01:04:34.536
The easy way
or the hard way.

1167
01:04:34.603 --> 01:04:36.705
That is such
a tough call. but...

1168
01:04:36.772 --> 01:04:40.409
Yeah. I'm gonna go
ahead and go with C.
none of the above!

1169
01:04:42.345 --> 01:04:44.347
I'm Amy. by the way.

1170
01:04:44.413 --> 01:04:46.615
Amy? From unbeWEAVEable?

1171
01:04:46.682 --> 01:04:47.950
Yeah.

1172
01:04:48.016 --> 01:04:52.154
I'm Maya.
My father talked
forever about you.

1173
01:04:52.221 --> 01:04:56.158
And I gotta say.
he really does like you.

1174
01:04:56.225 --> 01:04:57.960
I'm gonna throw up.

1175
01:04:58.827 --> 01:05:00.229
(GROANING)

1176
01:05:15.877 --> 01:05:17.246
Oh. that's not so bad.

1177
01:05:29.491 --> 01:05:31.193
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

1178
01:05:34.863 --> 01:05:36.232
PAUL: Oh. my God.

1179
01:05:37.866 --> 01:05:39.869
They've got his daughter.

1180
01:05:40.936 --> 01:05:40.936
Dad?

1181
01:05:40.936 --> 01:05:42.672
Maya.

1182
01:05:43.405 --> 01:05:44.907
Everything's gonna be okay.

1183
01:05:44.973 --> 01:05:46.108
How's your blood sugar?

1184
01:05:46.175 --> 01:05:49.278
Don't worry about me. okay?
I'm worried about you.

1185
01:05:49.344 --> 01:05:50.879
I love you.

1186
01:05:50.946 --> 01:05:53.516
All right. now.
I'm gonna get you all out.

1187
01:05:53.582 --> 01:05:56.352
You just hang in there.
okay. sweetie?

1188
01:05:56.418 --> 01:05:59.154
I will.
I'm a Blart. remember?

1189
01:05:59.221 --> 01:06:01.190
<i> Yeah. I'll see you soon.</i>

1190
01:06:03.492 --> 01:06:06.462
VECK: I'm supposed to be
on my way to the Cayman
Islands with the hostages.

1191
01:06:06.529 --> 01:06:09.898
And where the hell
is Rudolph? He should
be back by now.

1192
01:06:09.965 --> 01:06:11.968
(PAUL WHISTLES)

1193
01:06:50.639 --> 01:06:51.941
(YELLING)

1194
01:07:17.766 --> 01:07:22.938
"If Veck gets the codes.
he's taking us
to Cayman Islands"?

1195
01:07:23.004 --> 01:07:26.542
Well. Veck Sims.
welcome to the show.

1196
01:07:49.230 --> 01:07:50.765
Come and get me. Veck.

1197
01:07:50.832 --> 01:07:53.001
<i> I got your codes for
 the credit-card machines.</i>

1198
01:07:53.068 --> 01:07:56.071
Yo. you hear that?
That's Paul. baby!

1199
01:07:56.138 --> 01:07:58.474
(CHUCKLING) Blart?

1200
01:07:58.540 --> 01:08:00.242
That's who's been
screwing all this up?

1201
01:08:00.309 --> 01:08:02.945
You have got
to be kidding me.
Give me a radio.

1202
01:08:03.012 --> 01:08:04.713
Let me tell you something.

1203
01:08:04.780 --> 01:08:09.417
You take hostages in my mall.
you are making a big mistake.

1204
01:08:09.484 --> 01:08:11.520
You seriously undermissed...

1205
01:08:12.420 --> 01:08:13.823
(QUAVERING)

1206
01:08:14.856 --> 01:08:16.826
And you seriously...

1207
01:08:18.059 --> 01:08:19.261
Oh. no!

1208
01:08:20.895 --> 01:08:22.297
(MUMBLING)

1209
01:08:30.939 --> 01:08:32.975
Blart?

1210
01:08:38.580 --> 01:08:41.816
Sugar. Sugar.

1211
01:08:41.883 --> 01:08:44.587
<i> VECK: Blart?
 You there. Blart?</i>

1212
01:08:50.859 --> 01:08:52.828
Hello. Blart. You there?

1213
01:09:11.880 --> 01:09:13.282
(GRUNTING)

1214
01:09:17.018 --> 01:09:19.087
<i> VECK: Hey. Blart!</i>

1215
01:09:19.154 --> 01:09:22.258
I was hoping we could
get an ETA of when
you're gonna give up.

1216
01:09:24.024 --> 01:09:25.693
How about now?

1217
01:09:25.761 --> 01:09:29.264
I'll meet you on
the corner of Ne and Ver.

1218
01:09:29.331 --> 01:09:33.168
Yeah. you heard me. Never!

1219
01:09:33.234 --> 01:09:34.769
All right. Dad.

1220
01:09:35.337 --> 01:09:36.438
(LAUGHS)

1221
01:09:39.942 --> 01:09:43.546
Hey. fellas!
You looking for me?

1222
01:09:46.915 --> 01:09:49.919
Come on. Come on.
come on. Come on.

1223
01:09:55.457 --> 01:09:57.192
Follow me.

1224
01:09:57.259 --> 01:09:58.694
BLITZEN: There he is.

1225
01:10:02.264 --> 01:10:04.133
We got him trapped
in Rainforest Cafe.

1226
01:10:04.199 --> 01:10:07.202
Great. Wait for me.
You know.
my mom always said.

1227
01:10:07.268 --> 01:10:09.538
"If you want
something done right.
waste the guy yourself."

1228
01:10:09.604 --> 01:10:12.508
I'm paraphrasing.
of course.
You stay here.

1229
01:10:21.883 --> 01:10:23.786
Prancer. take the back.

1230
01:10:33.194 --> 01:10:34.797
(GROWLS)

1231
01:10:45.507 --> 01:10:46.942
(TRUMPETING)

1232
01:10:57.486 --> 01:10:58.654
(BEEPING)

1233
01:11:07.395 --> 01:11:08.664
(GRUNTS)

1234
01:11:12.367 --> 01:11:13.836
(BEEPING)

1235
01:11:31.553 --> 01:11:34.890
Hey. you.
Scuba Dooby-Doo.

1236
01:11:36.725 --> 01:11:37.993
(GRUNTS)

1237
01:11:57.278 --> 01:11:58.613
Hey. hey. hey. hey. hey.

1238
01:11:58.680 --> 01:12:00.682
Can I have my
codes now. please?

1239
01:12:00.749 --> 01:12:03.051
Why? No codes.
no Cayman Islands?

1240
01:12:03.118 --> 01:12:05.020
Looks like Paul Blart
turned into quite the
badass.

1241
01:12:05.087 --> 01:12:06.955
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
Relax.

1242
01:12:07.022 --> 01:12:08.490
(HISSING)

1243
01:12:08.557 --> 01:12:10.692
No.

1244
01:12:10.759 --> 01:12:13.829
